result.name: Wing Lai Yuen

reviews.text: one of the popular place in the area. been around for more than 30 years. famous for tom tom noodles. their spiceY dishes, steamed buns. expect wait at busY dinner hour

Best and the oldest, original Szechuan food restaurant in HK. Dishes are 90% similar to those I ate as a child. Prices reasonable n a big menu full of choices. Not all dishes are spicy, very tolerably spicy, n unique taste of Szechuan!
A very nice shanghaiese restaurant seving the neighbour. Foods are very good and cheap.
Great food, especially the tan-tan min, but expect to sit shoulder to shoulder with other eaters at the same table. Or arrive early, say 17:30.

Just alright, it's quite cheap but quality is not as good as expected. Average only. The spicy beef stir fried to go with the wrap is way too oily, doesnt have enough favour either. Tam tam noodle in peanut soup base wasn't special, handmade noodle was quite smooth and chewy tho. The deep fried bun is way too oily too, didn't fried good enough. Soy milk has a weird taste probably because of the plastic cups they use and clean. Sauce for the chicken cold dish wasn't good enough. So won't come back again unless very hungry and being nearby.

result.adr_address: 香港竹園鳳德道15號
result.name: 詠藜園四川菜館

reviews.text: 水準保持😋yummy午餐😋
擔擔麵👍
鑽石山老店常去，但當時是廿歲小子，今日第一次去鳳凰村店已相隔近五十年，下午茶時叚担担麪(26蚊平過雲吞麪)必試，加個肴肉很好，鄰桌大姐外賣两份豬脚不言而譽。
此食店交通不太方便，但食物味道很不錯，款式多及正統上海菜，維一不滿就是地方坐得不舒服，很窄。
在我來說是有太多回憶，在現代年輕一代並不喜歡，舖面太舊，味道太重。
